SIMPLE: discoverer
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Discoverer
<hw>Dis*cov"er*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who discovers; one who first comes to the knowledge of something; one who discovers an unknown country, or a new principle, truth, or fact.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>discoverers</qex> and searchers of the land.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Raleigh.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A scout; an explorer.</def>  <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Discoverment</ent>⟦br⟧
